B%20you%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20and%20you%20sat%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20hospital%20rooms.%20You%20had%20years%20of%20sleepless%20nights%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20something%20worked.%20They%20got%20clean%2C%20and%20they've%20remained%20so%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20kid%20made%20it%20through%2C%20but%20some%20wounds%20are%20so%20deep%20they%20leave%20scars.%20Scars%20that%20look%20like%20a%20father%20cutting%20their%20child%20out%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-much-does-it-cost-to-make-a-will%5C%22%3Ewill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20broken%20relationships%20with%20siblings%2C%20lifelong%20medical%20issues%2C%20and%20a%20mother%20who%20will%20do%20anything%20to%20keep%20the%20other%20shoe%20from%20dropping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20what%20your%20ex-husband%20and%20your%20other%20child%20might%20say%2C%20you%20aren't%20enabling%20your%20child%20by%20continuing%20to%20help%20them.%20You%20are%20helping%20them%20stay%20clean%20and%20helping%20your%20grandchildren%20have%20the%20life%20they%20deserve.%20Your%20kid%20was%20drowning%2C%20and%20you%20let%20them%20climb%20onto%20your%20raft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20have%20two%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20only%20a%20few%20hills%20I'm%20willing%20to%20die%20on%2C%20and%20one%20will%20always%20be%20that%20parents%20owe%20their%20children%20unconditional%20love.%20Period.%20No%20one%20else%20in%20the%20world%20owes%20them%20this.%20Not%20a%20spouse%2C%20sibling%2C%20friend%2C%20or%20even%20their%20children%20are%20obligated%20to%20love%20them%20without%20qualification.%20But%20when%20you%20have%20a%20child%2C%20you're%20making%20a%20commitment%20%E2%80%94%20yes%2C%20I'm%20bringing%20a%20human%20being%20into%20this%20scary%20world%2C%20but%20only%20because%20I%20promise%20they%20will%20always%20have%20my%20love%20to%20protect%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20right%2C%20love%20and%20like%20are%20different%20emotions%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20sound%20like%20your%20kid%20has%20tried%20to%20be%20likable%20in%20recent%20years.%20Looking%20at%20the%20timeline%20of%20your%20story%2C%20though%2C%20I%20think%20I%20may%20know%20why.%20You%20mentioned%20your%20child%20struggled%20with%20addiction%20for%2020%20years%2C%20which%2C%20adding%20their%20years%20of%20sobriety%2C%20means%20this%20has%20wrecked%20your%20family%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20ex-husband%20focused%20his%20attention%20and%20care%20on%20one%20child%20and%20you%20on%20the%20other.%20For%20their%20part%2C%20the%20siblings%20%26quot%3Bhate%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%20You%20mentioned%20how%20your%20child's%20addiction%20issues%20took%20years%20off%20your%20life%2C%20but%20your%20larger%20family%20dynamic%20tells%20me%20that%20it%20also%20broke%20your%20family%20in%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20how%20your%20other%20child%20felt%20during%20this%20breakdown.%20My%20guess%20is%20left%20out%20and%20overlooked.%20At%20best%2C%20held%20up%20as%20a%20flimsy%20poster%20child%20for%20their%20unfortunate%20sibling%20and%2C%20at%20worst%2C%20forgotten%20in%20the%20ceaseless%20drama%20of%20rehab%20facilities%2C%20hospital%20stays%2C%20and%20sleepless%20nights.%20You%20said%20the%20only%20time%20they%20talk%20to%20you%20is%20to%20scold%20you%20about%20their%20sibling%3B%20that%20sounds%20to%20me%20like%20they're%20angry%20at%20you%2C%20and%20they%20want%20you%20to%20know%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20you%20should%20appease%20them%20by%20abandoning%20your%20other%20child%2C%20financially%20or%20otherwise.%20But%20you%20should%20recognize%20that%20while%20love%20and%20like%20are%20different%20emotions%2C%20those%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20experience%20them%20exactly%20the%20same.%20One%20of%20your%20kids%20needs%20money.%20The%20other%20does%20not.%20But%20both%20of%20them%20need%20and%20deserve%20your%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20ways%20to%20honor%20both%20of%20your%20children.%20Keep%20doing%20what%20you're