0better%20and%20for%20worse%2C%20that's%20the%20way%20I%20am.%20That%20was%20good%2C%20now%20we've%20got%20to%20move%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParty%20leaders%20repeatedly%20urged%20throughout%20the%20week%20that%20for%20all%20the%20positivity%20coursing%20through%20the%20party%2C%20harder%20times%20are%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKamala%20Harris%20had%20a%20spectacular%20week%2C%20culminating%20a%20remarkable%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20senior%20Obama%20White%20House%20advisor%20David%20Axelrod%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20is%20a%20closely%20divided%20country%20and%20the%20race%20now%20will%20be%20a%20pitched%20struggle%20for%20every%20inch%20of%20terrain%20in%20the%20battleground%20states.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Trump%20tried%20to%20reclaim%20some%20attention%20by%20touting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frfk-jr-drops-out-presidential-race-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.'s%20endorsement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Kennedy's%20polling%20has%20crashed%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20but%20Trump%20hopes%20that%20in%20potentially%20an%20extremely%20close%20race%20the%20noted%20vaccine%20skeptic's%20supporters%20would%20push%20him%20over%20the%20edge%20in%20key%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20good%20news%20for%20President%20Trump%20and%20his%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20plain%20and%20simple%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20pollster%20Tony%20Fabrizio%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20released%20by%20the%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20vowed%20to%20try%20to%20take%20his%20name%20off%20the%20ballot%20in%2010%20swing%20states%2C%20though%20it%20remains%20uncertain%20if%20he%20will%20be%20able%20to%20do%20so%20in%20every%20effort.%20As%20election%20Law%20expert%20Derek%20T.%20Muller%20pointed%20out%20on%20X%2C%20Wisconsin%20only%20removes%20a%20candidate's%20name%20if%20they%20die%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20some%20sort%20of%20zombie%20candidacy%20could%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20major%20candidates%20are%20expected%20to%20return%20to%20the%20campaign%20trail%20in%20the%20days%20ahead%20before%20their%20first%20debate%20on%20September%2010%20in%20Philadelphia.%20It%20will%20be%20the%20first%20time%20Harris%20has%20ever%20met%20Harris%20and%20the%20first%20debate%20since%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20disastrous%20June%20performance%20altered%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20hope%20the%20arrival%20of%20debates%20will%20force%20Harris%20to%20confront%20her%20record.%20Harris%20has%20raced%20toward%20the%20center%20on%20key%20issues%20like%20healthcare%20and%20fracking%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20move%20beyond%20the%20progressive%20policy%20stances%20she%20took%20during%20her%202020%20Democratic%20primary%20campaign.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20campaign%20has%20tried%20to%20goad%20Harris%20into%20a%20sit-down%20interview%2C%20which%20would%20likely%20further%20explore%20her%20changing%20views.%20Still%2C%20thus%20far%2C%20she's%20focused%20on%20campaigning%20around%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20luxuriating%20in%20the%20free%20media%20attention%20her%20crowded%20rallies%20generate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20history%20holds%2C%20Harris'%20momentum%20could%20stretch%20even%20further.%20Candidates%20traditionally%20received%20a%20post-convention%20bump%20in%20polls.%20According%20to%20RealClearPolitics'%20polling%20average%2C%20Harris%20has%20a%20narrow%201.5%20percentage%20point%20lead%20in%20national%20polls.%20It's%20a%20sea%20change%20from%20Biden's%20consistent%20struggles%20but%20far%20from%20an%20insurmountable%20lead.%20In%201988%2C%20then-Massachusetts%20Gov.%20Michael%20Dukakis%20had%20a%2017-point%20lead%20in%20late%20July%20before%20Vice%20President%20George%20H.W.%20Bush%20overtook%20him%20and%20won%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20advisors%20tried%20to%20caution%20that%20Harris%20would%20rise%20in%20the%20polls%2C%20deeming%20this%20period%20her%20%26quot%3Bhoneymoon.%26quot%3B%20But%20so%20far%2C%20Trump%20has%20struggled%20to%20stick%20to%20a%20consistent%20attack%20on%20her.%20He's%20further%20reverted%20to%20form%20by%20undermining%20his%20message%20by%20claiming%20she's%20not%20really%20Black%20and%20feuding%20with%20fellow%20Republicans.%20On%20Thursday%20night%2C%20Trump%20tried%20to%20squash%20his%20beef%20with%20Georgia%20Gov.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-brian-kemp-relationship-georgia-election-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrian%20Kemp%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20perhaps%20moving%20beyond%20a%20renewed%20feud%20that%20threatened%20to%20derail%20his%20chances%20in%20a%20key%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20has%20also%20shaken%20up%20his%20campaign%20leadership%2C%20bringing%20former%202016%20campaign%20manager%20Corey%20Lewandowski%20back%20to%20the%20official%20fold.%20Trump%20wants%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trying-get-2016-magic-corey-lewandowski-wants-kellyanne-conway-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20find%20the%20magic%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20powered%20his%202016%20upset%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20successful%20that%20will%20be%20if%20he%20continues%20to%20stray%20from%20his%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20largest%20concerns%20for%20Harris%20is%20that%20Trump%20still%20leads%20on%20the%20metrics%20that%20are%20often%20fundamental%20to%20the%20race.%20Biden%20remains%20fairly%20unpopular.%20A%20Gallup%20poll%20found%2073%25%20of%20are%20dissatisfied%20with%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20country.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20some%20signs%20that%20Harris%20has%20narrowed%20Trump's%20strength%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20but%20a%20recent%20ABC%20News-Washington%20Post-Ipsos%20poll%20found%20he%20still%20held%20a%209-percentage%20point%20advantage%20over%20Harris%20when%20voters%20were%20asked%20who%20they%20trusted%20to%20handle%20it%20more.%20Trump%20also%20had%20a%2010-point%20advantage%20on%20immigration.%2