%20not%20only%20write%20a%20better%20prompt%2C%20but%20you%20can%20also%20triangulate%20better%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20older%20workers%20don't%20always%20get%20the%20chance.%20Surveys%2C%20including%20one%20from%20Generation%2C%20suggest%20that%20many%20people%20in%20charge%20of%20hiring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.generation.org%2Fnews%2Fthe-midcareer-opportunity-new-research-from-generation-and-oecd%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavor%20younger%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20though%20the%20same%20managers%20report%20that%20the%20older%20workers%20they've%20brought%20on%20have%20worked%20out%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20important%20finding%20because%20while%20the%20job%20market%20is%20still%20strong%2C%20it%20has%20cooled%20from%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago.%20That's%20led%20some%20job%20seekers%20who%20aren't%20fresh%20out%20of%20school%20to%20report%20they've%20struggled%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultiple-job-interviews-a-pain-but-also-benefit-workers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinding%20new%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20in%20areas%20like%20tech%2C%20where%20employers%20have%20cut%20back%20and%20where%20youth%20is%20lionized%20in%20industry%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ef007b3-6532-4df0-9342-7f61884b254f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOlder%20workers%20face%20headwinds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Generation%20survey%2C%20conducted%20with%20the%20%3Cspan%3EOrganization%20for%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Development%2C%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3Efour%20in%2010%20employers%20said%20they%20would%20hire%20someone%20between%20ages%2020%20and%2029.%20About%20half%20said%20they%20would%20choose%20people%20ages%2030%20to%2044.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20workers%20older%20than%20that%2C%20the%20picture%20is%20less%20bright%3A%20Only%20about%20one-third%20of%20employers%20said%20they%20would%20hire%20someone%20aged%2045%20to%2054.%20And%20above%20age%2055%2C%20employers'%20willingness%20to%20hire%20drops%20to%2013%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMourshed%20said%20those%20headwinds%20are%20a%20key%20reason%20that%2040%25%20of%20the%20long-term%20unemployed%20in%20the%20US%20are%20mid-career%2C%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshocked-when-recruiter-said-too-old-tech-job-ageism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVern%20Six%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who's%20in%20his%20late%2050s%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20his%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20working%20in%20tech%20have%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20him%20to%20get%20a%20new%20role.%20One%20recruiter%2C%20after%20reviewing%20his%20experience%2C%20said%20he%20was%20surprised%20that%20Six%20wasn't%20a%20chief%20technology%20officer%2C%20Six%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recruiter%20went%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20hard%20sell.%20I%20don't%20even%20know%20if%20I%20can%20pitch%20you%20to%20any%20of%20my%20clients.%20They're%20all%20going%20to%20wonder%20why%20you're%20not%20a%20CTO%20or%20at%20the%20C-level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20said%20he%20was%20stunned%20the%20recruiter%20would%20say%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ddc3290-7189-4b77-91e4-e6aa86076190%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFocus%20on%20ability%2C%20not%20age%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20problem%20facing%20older%20workers%20is%20that%20they%20can%20be%20judged%20on%20their%20age%2C%20not%20their%20experience%20or%20their%20ability%20and%20willingness%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarga%20Biller%2C%20senior%20project%20director%20at%20Harvard%20University's%20Learning%20Innovations%20Laboratory%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20desire%20to%20learn%20matters%20more%20than%20age.%20Older%20workers%20can%20keep%20up%20with%20their%20younger%20counterparts%20as%20long%20as%20those%20with%20more%20experience%20aren't%20too%20wedded%20to%20how%20they've%20done%20things%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20back%20to%20the%20mindset%2C%20'How%20well%20can%20you%20learn%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20learning%20on%20the%20job%20often%20takes%20dedication%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20a%20willingness%20to%20shift%20how%20work%20gets%20done.%20It's%20easy%2C%20for%20example%2C%20for%20workers%20of%20any%20age%20to%20report%20using%20AI.%20But%20some%20might%20dabble%20while%20others%20go%20deep.%20That%20can%20make%20a%20difference%2C%20according%20to%20Karie%20Willyerd%2C%20chief%20learning%20officer%20in%20residence%20at%20the%20training%20platform%20Skillable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20could%20both%20say%20we%20have%20the%20habit%20of%20using%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20Copilot%20or%20ChatGPT%20all%20day%20long%2C%20but%20we%20could%20be%20using%20it%20in%20very%20different%20ways%20based%20on%20our%20mindset%20about%20what%20it%20can%20do%20and%20not%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20that%20dismiss%20older%20workers%20risk%20missing%20out%20on%20strong%20talent%2C%20according%20to%20Tom%20Murray%2C%20president%20of%20the%20executive%20search%20and%20leadership%20advisory%20firm%20Heidrick%20%26amp%3B%20Struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20one%20role%20seeing%20strong%20growth%20is%20the%20chief%20AI%20officer.%20Murray%20said%20that's%20the%20type%20of%20job%20where%20know-how%20around%20managing%20teams%20and%20setting%20strategy%20is%20important.%20Experience%20can%20pay%20big%20dividends%20for%20those%20types%20of%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20run%20orgs%20that%20are%20that%20are%20very%20scaled%20%E2%80%94%20that%20everyone%20feels%20like%20will%20most%20likely%20be%20the%20fastest-growing%20organization%20within%20their%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Murray%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20many%20employers%20are%20rightly%20focused%20on%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20talent%20through%20hiring%20and%20helping%20build%20the%20skills%20of%20their%20existing%20workforce.%20He%20said%20it's%20also%20important%20for%20employers%20to%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20snagging%20more%20experienced%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20attract%2C%20develop%2C%20and%20retain%20that%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20Murray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20both%20older%20and%20younger%20workers%20can%20face%20challenges%20when%20those%20doing%20the%20hiring%20are%20of%20a%20different%20generation.%20In%20early%202024%2C%20Resume%20Builder%20reported%20that%20about%20one-third%20of%20hiring%20managers%20said%20they%20were%20biased%20against%20Gen%20Z%20candidates.%20A%20similar%20proportion%20voiced%20concerns%20about%20hiring%20candidates%20over%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20pitfalls%20like%20age%20bias%2C%26quot%3B%20Stacie%20Haller%2C%20the%20chief%20career%20advisor%20at%20Resume%20Builder%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20know%20the%20landscape%20you're%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-older-workers-better-than-younger-could-help-hiring-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724579222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8e0191aa2ac29ee33d517%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-older-workers-better-than-younger-could-help-hiring-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20experienced%20workers%20can%20excel%20with%20AI%2C%20often%20matching%20or%20surpassing%20younger%20peers%2C%20yet%20age%20bias%20persists%20and%20can%20hurt%20older%20job%20seekers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-older-workers-better-than-younger-could-help-hiring-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22