inessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-productivity-advisor-tips-work-email-meetings-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproductive%20times%20for%20some%20of%20Google's%20top%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20her%20method%20is%20surprisingly%20pretty%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BUptime%3A%20A%20Practical%20Guide%20to%20Personal%20Productivity%20and%20Wellbeing%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said%20that%20each%20person%20has%20different%20high%20and%20low%20energy%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20are%20night%20owls%20and%20some%20people%20can%20function%20well%20at%205%3A00%20a.m.%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20built%20into%20our%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20uncover%20these%20internal%20clocks%2C%20the%20first%20question%20she%20asks%20executives%20in%20her%20coaching%20sessions%20is%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20had%20an%20entire%20day%20tomorrow%2C%20with%20no%20meetings%2C%20no%20interruptions%2C%20no%20standing%20commitments%2C%20but%20a%20bunch%20of%20things%20to%20get%20done%2C%20how%20would%20you%20structure%20your%20day%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20answers%20varied%20drastically.%20Some%20clients%20preferred%20working%20into%20the%20evening%20after%20late%20lunches%2C%20while%20others%20liked%20starting%20at%20dawn%20with%20an%20afternoon%20break%20or%20workout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20everyone%20has%20their%20%26quot%3Bpower%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20Martin%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20two%20to%20three%20hours%20a%20day%20that%20you%20feel%20your%20most%20productive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20suggests%20keeping%20a%20little%20notepad%20by%20your%20desk%20for%20two%20weeks%20and%20writing%20down%20any%20time%20you%20feel%20particularly%20productive%20or%20have%20low%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20you've%20come%20up%20with%20some%20of%20your%20general%20productivity%20patterns%2C%20you%20can%20start%20mimicking%20your%20ideal%20conditions%20as%20often%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20Martin%20said%20these%20power%20hours%20would%20be%20spent%20on%20tasks%20related%20to%20your%20top%20three%20priorities.%20If%20they%20partially%20overlap%20with%20other%20fixed%20commitments%20like%20mandatory%20meetings%2C%20Martin%20recommends%20blocking%20your%20power%20hours%20to%20whatever%20degree%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20one%20to%20three%20times%20a%20week%2C%20or%20even%20just%20one%20hour%20of%20your%20three%20Power%20Hours%2C%20will%20make%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20how%20much%20control%20you%20feel%20over%20your%20work%20and%20to-do%20lists%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20said%20that%20multiple%20clients%20have%20told%20her%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20one%20single%20shift%20in%20their%20schedule%20has%20made%20the%20biggest%20difference%20in%20their%20overall%20productivity.%26quot%3B%20In%20one%20case%2C%20an%20executive%20used%20to%20take%20her%20lunch%20break%20at%20noon%20every%20day%20before%20realizing%20that%20it%20fell%20right%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20when%20she%20felt%20most%20productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20started%20taking%20a%20later%20lunch%20and%20found%20that%20the%2012%3A00-1%3A00%20p.m.%20hour%20was%20one%20of%20her%20most%20productive%20hours%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20think%20she%20used%20to%20spend%20it%20eating%20lunch!%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20you're%20confined%20to%20only%20working%20during%20those%20high-energy%20hours.%20What%20Martin%20calls%20%26quot%3Boff-peak%20Hours%26quot%3B%20are%20great%20for%20other%20activities%20like%20quick%20emails%20or%20coffee%20chats.%20They%20can%20also%20actually%20be%20optimal%20for%20more%20creative%20undertakings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20cited%20research%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.albion.edu%2Fnews-article%2Fpsychologys-mareike-wieth-flies-high-with-media%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMareike%20Wieth%3C%