Findustry%2Fnews%2Findia-s-corporate-mobility-market-thrives-amidst-rising-demand-report-124082500135_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BSo%20Painful%20I%20Couldn't%20Sleep%26quot%3B%3A%20African%20Man%20Shares%20Horrifying%20Symptoms%20Of%20Mpox%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20designated%20Mpox%20a%20public%20health%20emergency%20of%20international%20concern%20for%20the%20second%20time%20in%20two%20years.%20The%20decision%20stemmed%20from%20the%20rapid%20spread%20of%20a%20new%2C%20extremely%20dangerous%20form%20of%20the%20virus%20across%20Africa.%20Outbreaks%20have%20been%20reported%20in%20Burundi%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Rwanda%20and%20Uganda%20since%20July.%20A%20case%20of%20the%20new%20strain%20has%20also%20been%20detected%20in%20Sweden.%20Over%20570%20people%20have%20died%20from%20the%20disease%20so%20far.%20Amid%20this%2C%20an%20African%20man%2C%20who%20contracted%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fa-list-of-countries-with-confirmed-cases-of-new-mpox-variant-6404124%5C%22%3Enew%20strain%3C%2Fa%3E%20'Clade%201b'%20of%20Mpox%20recently%20shared%20the%20torturing%20symptoms%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgide%20Irambona%2C%2040%2C%20from%20Burundi's%20main%20city%2C%20Bujumbura%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcly3xzdq909o%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20the%20disease%20causes%20horrible%20pain.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20swollen%20lymph%20nodes%20in%20my%20throat.%20It%20was%20so%20painful%20I%20couldn't%20sleep.%20Then%20the%20pain%20subsided%20there%20and%20it%20moved%20to%20my%20legs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Compared%20to%20other%20Mpox%20variations%2C%20Clade%201b%20is%20more%20contagious%20but%20appears%20to%20be%20less%20deadly.%20It%20is%20primarily%20transmitted%20through%20heterosexual%20transmission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20in%20treatment%20at%20the%20King%20Khaled%20University%20Hospital%20for%20nine%20days%20now%2C%20sharing%20a%20room%20with%20two%20other%20patients.%20He%20thinks%20a%20friend%20may%20have%20given%20him%20the%20contagious%20virus.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20friend%20who%20had%20blisters.%20I%20think%20I%20got%20it%20from%20him.%20I%20did%20not%20know%20it%20was%20Mpox.%20Thankfully%20our%20seven%20children%20have%20not%20shown%20any%20signs%20of%20having%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Irambona's%20wife%20has%20also%20contracted%20the%20disease%20and%20is%20being%20looked%20after%20at%20the%20same%20facility.%20Of%20the%2061%20available%20beds%2C%2059%20are%20filled%20by%20infected%20patients%2C%20of%20these%2C%20a%20third%20are%20under%20the%20age%20of%2015.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%2C%20children%20are%20the%20most%20affected%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20at%20the%20hospital%2C%20Odette%20Nsavyimana%2C%20said%20that%20the%20number%20of%20patients%20is%20increasing%20daily.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20now%20setting%20up%20tents%20outside.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20three%20tents%20currently%2C%20one%20for%20suspected%20cases%2C%20a%20second%20for%20triage%20and%20another%20for%20confirmed%20cases%20before%20they%20can%20be%20sent%20to%20wards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20tough%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20babies%20come.%20They%20cannot%20stay%20alone%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20keep%20their%20mothers%20here%20as%20well.%20Even%20if%20they%20have%20no%20symptoms...%20It%20is%20such%20a%20tough%20situation.%20I%20am%20worried%20about%20the%20numbers.%20If%20they%20keep%20increasing%2C%20there%20is%20no%20capacity%20for%20us%20to%20handle%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Nsavyimana%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedical%20authorities%20are%20concerned%20about%20scarce%20resources.%20There%20isn't%20a%20vaccine%2C%20nor%20enough%20testing%20kits%2C%20and%20only%20one%20lab%20in%20the%20nation%20that%20can%20test%20blood%20samples%20for%20the%20virus.%20It%20is%20also%20difficult%20to%20maintain%20hygienic%20conditions%20throughout%20Bujumbura%20due%20to%20the%20city's%20restricted%20access%20to%20necessities%20like%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Public%20Health%20Emergency%20Operations%20expressed%20her%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20near%20future.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20real%20challenge.%20The%20fact%20that%20diagnosis%20is%20only%20done%20in%20one%20place%20delays%20detecting%20new%20cases.%20Health%20centres%20are%20calling%20the%20laboratory%20saying%20they%20have%20suspected%20cases%2C%20but%20it%20takes%20time%20for%20teams%20from%20the%20lab%20to%20deploy%20to%20where%20the%20suspected%20cases%20are%20to%20take%20samples%2C%26quot%3B%20Liliane%20Nkengurutse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20many%20people%20living%20there%20are%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-is-mpox-how-it-spreads-critical-symptoms-and-more-6409144%5C%22%3EMpox%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20are%20carrying%20on%20life%20as%20usual.%20%26quot%3BMany%20people%20do%20not%20understand%20the%20gravity%20of%20this%20issue.%20Even%20where%20there%20have%20been%20cases%2C%20people%20still%20just%20mingle%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Nkengurutse%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20residents%20said%20that%20they%20did%20not%20know%20that%20Mpox%20was%20spreading%20in%20the%20country.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20heard%20about%20this%20disease%2C%20but%20I%20have%20never%20seen%20someone%20who%20suffers%20from%20it.%20I%20have%20only%20seen%20it%20on%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20it%20affects%20babies%20and%20young%20people.%20I%20am%20scared%20of%20it%2C%20but%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20I%20will%20just%20stay%20at%20home.%20I%20have%20to%20work.%20My%20family%20has%20to%20eat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%2